This paper is primarily focused on fair machine learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). However, the paper also deals with privacy protection of demographic data, which is a topic of interest in computer security (cs.CR) and cyber privacy (cs.CY). The distributed nature of the proposed framework involves communication between different parties, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the development and evaluation of machine learning models, which could also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
